<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Reports Bosnian Muslim, Croatian Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2402124594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0737 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2402124594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, February 23 (XINHUA) -- A ceasefire 
agreement signed by Bosnia Muslim Commander Rasim Delich and 
Croatian Commander Ante Roso in Zagreb tonight will become 
effective at 12 a.m. February 25. 
  Under the agreement, the two sides will end hostilities in 
all disputed areas of Bosnia-Herzegovina and the U.N. 
peacekeeping force will be deployed to supervise implementation 
of the ceasefire. 

