<H3> <TI>   RENMIN RIBAO To Publish Local Editions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2502033894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0250 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2502033894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 25 (XINHUA) -- With the approval 
of the Central Committee of the ruling Communist Party of China 
(CPC), the "PEOPLE'S DAILY", [RENMIN RIBAO] China's leading 
national newspaper, is to publish local editions. 
  The newspaper today quoted its director Shao Huaze as saying 
that, as a first step, the east China edition of the newspaper 
is to be published in Shanghai as of January 1, 1995. 
  Publication of the local editions is aimed at publicizing in 
a more timely fashion the principles and policies of the CPC and 
transmitting information about local economic and social 
development more fully, Shao explained. 
  He revealed that Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the CPC 
central committee, and other members of the Standing Committee 
of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee have all 
given important instructions on further improving the newspaper, 
the organ of the CPC Central Committee. 

</TEXT>

