  The two sides also exchanged views on the further expansion 
of cooperation and China's linking up with IDB. 
  Iglesias arrived in China on February 20 at the invitation 
of 
the People's Bank of China. 
  IDB is the oldest regional inter-governmental bank, with the 
largest business volume and capital. It has played an important 
role in promoting economic development and social progress in 
Latin American countries. 
  Iglesias' visit here, wound up this afternoon, has 
strengthened the mutual understanding and existing friendship 
between China and IDB, said sources from the People's Bank of 
China. 

