<H3> <TI>   India Opposes Introduction of Discriminatory NPT Regime </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2502165294 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2502165294 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] India has rejected a backdoor introduction of the 
discriminatory Nuclear Nonproliferation Treaty, NPT, regime. 
Indian experts told a workshop on nuclear disarmament at 
Shanghai in China that India firmly opposes any move to 
introduce discriminatory regime in the circulation of material 
needed for nuclear fission. Experts from India, China, the 
United States, and Pakistan are attending the workshop. 

</TEXT>

