<F P=100> United States &amp; Canada </F>
<H3> <TI>   Morgan Stanley Financial Company Opens Shanghai Office </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2502180494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1530 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2502180494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, February 25 (XINHUA) -- The Shanghai 
office of the Morgan Stanley group of the United States opened 
today, John Mack, president of the global financial institution, 
announced here. 
  The reason the group has chosen Shanghai for its first 
office 
in China is that the city is becoming China's financial center, 
Mack said at a ceremony to mark the opening of the office. 
  He said, "I am sure that China will play an increasingly 
important role in the global financial market." 
  Therefore, the Chinese market has become the focus of the 
group's operations, he said. The Shanghai office will offer 
consultancy and advice on how to turn Chinese enterprises into 
shareholding companies, he added. 
  According to Mack, the office will also help Chinese 
companies issue shares in the United States and Europe; help 
Chinese securities institutions enter the international market; 
become involved in issuing shares in China's securities markets; 
offer advice on how to raise money for large industrial and 
infrastructural projects in China; and seek opportunities for 
cooperation with Chinese financial institutions. 
  The Morgan Stanley group intends to undertake a large real 
estate project and plans to participate in foreign exchange and 
futures trading in Shanghai, he said. 
  The group is applying to open another office in Beijing, he 
said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

