<F P=103> OW2702124094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Osaka, February 27 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice Premier 
Zhu Rongji arrived in Osaka this evening on the second leg of a 
nine-day visit which takes in a first-hand look at corporate 
activities in Japan's western and southwestern areas. 
  During his two-day stay in the industrial hub, Zhu will meet 
a group of business leaders including Toyota Motor Corp. 
President Tatsuro Toyoda. 
  He is expected to brief them about the Chinese reform on a 
shift to a market economy and urge them to expand trade and 
economic cooperation with China. 
  He is scheduled to visit the recently completed Kansai New 
International Airport and a clothing wholesale market on Monday. 
  The vice premier will also travel to Kagawa and Fukuoka 
Prefectures and leaves for home on March 4. 

