<H3> <TI>   Aftermath of Political Reform Accord Reported </TI></H3>
<H4>   Diet Enacts Reform Bills </H4>
<F P=102> OW2901091594 Tokyo KYODO in English 0859 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2901091594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Tokyo, Jan. 29 KYODO -- The Diet enacted the 
government-proposed political reform bills Saturday [29 January] 
whose key elements are set to be revised at the regular Diet 
session slated to convene on Monday in line with a compromise 
reached between Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa and opposition 
Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) President Yohei Kono. 
  The enactment came on the last day of the current 
extraordinary Diet session, the deadline set by Hosokawa, who 
had staked his political fortunes on passage of the package. 
  The House of Councillors approved the package in a plenary 
session after the House of Representatives passed it. Each 
chamber gave its blessing to the measures by a stand-up vote. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

