<H3> <TI>   Assembly Chairman Sees European Parliamentarians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3101160794 Hanoi VNA in English 1537 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK3101160794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA Jan. 31 -- Chairman of the Vietnam 
National Assembly Nong Duc Manh, this afternoon received were 
the visiting delegation of the European Parliament. [sentence as 
received] 
  At the reception, Senator Ben Visser, head of the 
delegation, 
informed Chairman Nong Duc Manh of the European Parliament's 
activities in 1993 with a view of promoting the relations 
between the countries in the European Community and Vietnam. 
  For his part, Charman Nong Duc Manh hailed the positive 
contributions of the European Parliament, and expressed his 
thanks to the European Parliament for its wish for the 
establishment of the relations between the Vietnam National 
Assembly and the European Parliament and for inviting a 
delegation of the Vietnamese NA to visit the European Parliament. 
  Mr. Nong Duc Manh and Senator Ben Visser hailed the 
delegation's visit, as the beginning of a new stage of relations 
of cooperation, friendship and development between Vietnam and 
the EC's countries, and between Vietnam and the European 
Parliament. 
  Early during the day, the delegation held talks with a 
delegation of Vietnam's National Assembly led by deputy head of 
the External Relations Commission Phan Quang. 
  At the talks, Senator Ben Visser said that a programme of 
cooperation with Vietnam was being drafted. He also expressed 
his hope that a frame-work agreement on trade and economic 
cooperation between Vietnam and the European Parliament would be 
signed soon. 
  For his part, Mr Phan Quang spoke about the issues of common 
concern aimed at further promoting the possibilities of 
cooperation and mutual assistance between the Vietnam National 
Assembly and the European Parliament in the spirit of 
friendship, equality and mutual benifit. 

</TEXT>

