<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA Jan. 31 -- A delegation of the Western 
Australian parliament, led by its PM, Williams Thomas [name and 
title as received], held talks today with a delegation of 
Vietnam's National Assembly, led by Prof. Dr. Vu Dinh Cu, member 
of the National Assembly's Standing Committee and head of the 
Commission for Science, Technology and Environment (CSTE). The 
Western Australian delegation arrived here yesterday. 
  At the talks Dr Vu Dinh Cu informed the guests of the 
National Assembly's activities in general and the activities of 
the CSTE in particular, and of the important major achievements 
recorded by the Vietnamese people in the renovation process for 
national construction and some issues of common concern. 
  For his part, Mr. Williams Thomas briefed the Western 
Australian parliament's activities over the past time. He also 
touched on bilateral matters for the interests of each country 
and for peace and development in the region. 
  The two sides also discussed concrete steps to enhance the 
friendly and cooperative relations and mutual assistance between 
the two legislatures. 
  On the same day, the Australian delegation had working 
sessions with officials of the Ministry of Science, Technology 
and Environment, the Directorate General of Post and 
Telecommunications and others. 

