<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Participation in Economic Activities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3001144594 Hanoi VNA in English 1338 GMT 30 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK3001144594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA Jan.30 -- The armed forces last year 
increased their participation in economic production and 
business with the total turnover of VN dong 1,800 billion 
(roughly USD 170 million), up by 44 per cent compared with 1992 
figure. 
  They contributed VND 120 billion to the state budget, an 
increase of 30 per cent, and gained an export value of USD 90 
million, up by 47.5 per cent over 1992. They also made a 
combined investment of USD 147 million in some joint venture 
projects with foreign partners. 
  Moreover they joined in the state's economic projects and 
programmes of afforestation, the construction of a motor highway 
linking Hanoi and the international airport of Noi Bai, the 
construction of the Yali Hydro-Electric Plant in central 
Vietnam, the construction of an export processing zone in 
Haiphong port city, and the 500 kv trans-Vietnam power line. 

</TEXT>

