<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ranariddh Asks for Canadian Assistance </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0102083494 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0430 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0102083494 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0430 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On the afternoon of 31 January, yesterday, Prince 
Krompreah Norodom Ranariddh, first prime minister, received His 
Excellency [H.E.] (Howard Balloch), assistant of the Canadian 
minister of foreign affairs and foreign trade, for talks. 
  Prince Krompreah thanked Canada profoundly for its attention 
and assistance to Cambodia regarding the Geneva conference, the 
Paris peace agreement, and mine clearing. Furthermore, Prince 
Krompreah proposed that Canada assist in building hydropower 
dams, communications, and power plants; and in giving 
professional training to the Khmer Royal Armed Forces. He also 
suggested that Canada send businessmen to invest in Cambodia. 
  H.E. (Howard Balloch) disclosed that Canada will continue to 
provide more assistance in clearing mines in Cambodia. As for 
other proposals put forward by Prince Krompreah, he said he will 
convey them to the Canadian Government so that the latter can 
assist in these matters. 

</TEXT>

