<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   NADK on `Total Defeat' of Anlung Veng Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0102030194 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0102030194 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The large-scale offensive by the Vietnamese 
communist puppets -- under the command of the Vietnamese 
communists -- and their alliance suffered total defeat on 31 
January 1994. 
  1. The large-scale offensive by the Vietnamese communists 
and their alliance began on 1 January in an attempt to open up 
the Route 69 battlefield and head toward Anlung Veng from 
Samraong, Sre Noy, and Kulen. The puppet forces mobilized 70 
percent of their forces from all over the country to concentrate 
on this battlefield. Ninety percent of the puppet commanders 
were sent to direct the fight on this battlefield. 
  2. Very tense and fierce fighting has been underway on 
this battlefield for a full month. 
  3. On 31 January, the National Army of Democratic 
Kampuchea [NADK] and the people attacked and totally smashed 
this large-scale campaign launched by the Vietnamese communist 
puppets, under the command of the Vietnamese communists; their 
alliance; and the two-headed government. 
  4. On 31 January, the NADK and the people captured four 
tanks, two armored personnel carriers, and six military trucks 
in an area east of Bak Nim after these vehicles stumbled into an 
ambush by the NADK and the people. The NADK and the people 
captured three other tanks and three military trucks east of Sre 
Noy. They killed over 100 enemy troops and wounded over 100 
more. Several hundred survivors have retreated. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

