<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Group of 803 Refugees Returns From PRC </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0102034894 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 0000 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0102034894 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lao </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A group of 803 Lao refugees from 63 families has 
returned home from southern China. The ceremony to hand over 
the refugees was held on 27 January at the Lao-Chinese border 
checkpoint between Bosin, Laos and (Bohan), China. The ceremony 
was jointly officiated by Ang Chitdala, head of the Luang Namtha 
Province Labor and Social Welfare Service, and (Li Tokou), head 
of the Civil Service in Yunnan Province, PRC. Witnessing the 
event were representatives of the Lao Consulate in Kunming and 
of the UNHCR representative offices in Laos, the PRC, and Geneva. 
  This is the first repatriation of Lao refugees in 1994. So 
far, more than 2,900 out of approximately 4,000 Lao refugees in 
southern China have returned to their motherland. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

