<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prasong Visit to Chile, Argentina Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0102083294 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 0530 GMT 
1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0102083294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Thai </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Foreign Ministry's Information Department has 
reported on Foreign Minister Squadron Leader Prasong Sunsiri's 
visit to the Republic of Chile between 25 and 27 January. The 
foreign minister stressed Thailand's policy of friendship with 
all countries, especially its relations with other countries in 
ASEAN and APEC [Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation]. Chile will 
become an APEC member in 1994. Thailand wants to see Chile 
become an economic and trade center in Latin America or serve as 
a commercial gateway for ASEAN as well as Indochinese countries. 
  The foreign minister visited Argentina between 27 and 30 
January. He met with the Argentine foreign minister during the 
visit. The two sides discussed ways of further strengthening 
bilateral relations and cooperation as well as economic and 
investment cooperation. The two sides set a target for 
bilateral trade at U.S. $200 million annually. In addition, the 
two sides discussed ways of strengthening bilateral contacts and 
exchanges of officials in the cultural, linguistic, political, 
diplomatic, trade, and technological fields; they also discussed 
cooperation among members of the private sector. 
  Meanwhile, the foreign minister and his delegation is 
visiting New Orleans in the United States. He will proceed to 
Los Angeles on 2 February. 

</TEXT>

