<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA Jan. 27 -- A delegation of the Austrian 
Ministry of Foreign Affairs led by its General Secretary Dr. 
Wolfgang Schallenberg left Hanoi today, concluding its threeday 
visit to Vietnam. 
  While here the delegation paid a tribute to President Ho Chi 
Minh at his mausoleum. It was received by Deputy Prime Minister 
Tran Duc Luong and Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam. 
  The Austrian delegation also held talks with a delegation of 
the Vietnamese Foreign Ministry headed by Deputy Foreign 
Minister Nguyen Dy Nien. The two sides noted with satisfaction 
at positive steps in the development of the relations between 
the two countries in the recent time and agreed that the 
friendship and cooperation between the two countries should be 
push up to commensurate with the potentials and desire of the 
two sides [sentence as received]. He also affirmed Austria's 
wish for further development of bilateral relations in the new 
situation of each country and each region. 
  For its part, the Vietnamese side welcomed the intention of 
the Austrian Government and businessmen and industrialists to 
promote their relations of economic, scientific and 
technological cooperation with Vietnam. The Vietnamese 
Government has created favourable conditions for the development 
of bilateral relations in the interests of the two peoples, and 
for peace and cooperation in the region and the world. 
  The two sides exchanged views on international issues of 
common concern. 

