<H3> <TI>   Training Pact With Czech Republic, Slovakia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0102143894 Hanoi VNA in English 1422 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0102143894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA February 1 -- A delegation of the Ministry 
of Education and Training led by its Deputy Minister Tran Chi 
Dao has recently visited Czech and Slovakia. On Jan. 26, the 
Vietnamese deputy minister and Mr. J. Vodika, minister of Labour 
and Social Affairs of Czech signed an agreement on training jobs 
for Vietnamese and protocol on the implementation of the 
above-said agreement for 1994. Another agreement was signed by 
Mr. Dao and Mrs. O. Kentosava, minister of labour and social 
affairs of Slovakia, for the same purpose. Under these 
agreements, some 250 Vietnamese will attend classes at schools 
for job training in Czech and Slovakia this year. 

