<H3> <TI>   Further on Visit by U.S. Religious Delegation </TI></H3>
<H4>   Graham, Delegation Visit Mangyongdae </H4>
<F P=102> SK2901112294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1049 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2901112294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- Visiting U.S. 
religious leader Rev. Billy Graham and his party Friday 
visited Mangyongdae, the home village of the great leader 
President Kim Il-song. 
  The guests saw with keen interest mementos hearing immortal 
stories about the historic old home. 
  Concluding the visit, the pastor said President Kim Il-song 
was born into a poor family and grew up, cultivating his 
strength and courage. 
  The guests posed for a souvenir picture in front of the old 
home. 
  They also visited Kim Il-song University Friday. 
  While going round the revolutionary museum of the 
university, 
they were told that the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il 
strengthened the university into a chuche-based centre of native 
cadre training with his outstanding idea, theory and activity. 
  Then, the guests had a talk with teachers and students of 
the 
university. 
  Rev. Billy Graham told them that the visit deeply impressed 
him and that the university is a good place. 
  The guests visited the Three Revolution Exhibition Saturday. 
  Earlier, they met with officials of the C.C. [Central 
Committee], the Korean Christians Federation. 

</TEXT>

