<H3> <TI>   Radio Denounces `War Exercises' in South </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2901125194 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2100 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2901125194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2100 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to report on Cheil [KBS-1 Radio Network] 
Radio in Seoul, troops from the puppet Capital Defense Command 
on 27 January staged war exercises three times during the day 
and night by blindly firing rifles in the area around Mt. Umyong 
in Seoul. Because of war exercise commotions, residents in 
Socho-ku and Kwanak-ku in Seoul, and in Kwachon City, were 
terror-stricken all day. 
  On 21 January, troops from the puppet Capital Defense 
Command 
also staged a war exercise by blindly firing rifles in areas 
around Socho-ku, Seoul, thus arousing a protest from the 
residents. 
  The war exercise commotions staged every day by the South 
Korean puppet clique, which is advertising itself as a civilian 
government, outdistances the war frenzy of successive military 
fascist dictators. Such commotions are part of desperate 
maneuvers designed to divert the attention of the people, who 
are filled with complaints against the incumbent regime. 
  The South Korean people will never tolerate the maneuvers of 
the civilian warmongers who are attempting to evade the crisis 
in their rule by war exercise commotions. 

</TEXT>

