<F P=106> ["`Civilian' Dictatorship Brandishing Sword at Ideology" -- </F>
KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- NODONG SINMUN today 
comments on the brutal suppression of the followers of the 
chuche idea by the South Korean fascist clique these days. 
Declaring that ideology can never be bound in chain, the 
analyst says: 
  Some time ago, the puppet Kwangju District Court passed 
prison terms on five students of Chonnam National University who 
had studied the chuche idea. 
  Kim Yong-sam, who ruthlessly tramples upon the freedom of 
the 
choice of ideology and quest of truth, while advertising 
"civilian politics," is a political hooligan and tyrant not 
different in the least from the preceding military dictators. 
  His group is trying to keep off the attraction of the great 
chuche idea and incite North-South confrontation, resorting to 
bayonet. But it is a foolish act. 
  The more frantic Kim Yong-sam gets in brandishing the 
bayonet, the stronger the resistance of the people will grow and 
the clearer it will reveal to the world its ignorance and 
incompetency as a ruler without a philosophy worthy of being 
followed by the people. 
  The puppets must guarantee the people the freedom of choice 
of ideology and the quest of truth and release the illegally 
arrested students. 

</TEXT>

