<H3> <TI>   Bhutto Receives DPRK Envoy; Comments on Succession </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK3001085094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0825 GMT 30 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3001085094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 30 (KCNA) -- Pakistani Prime 
Minister Benazir Bhutto mentioned the friendly relations between 
Pakistan and Korea when she received DPRK ambassador to her 
country on Jan. 25. 
  She said the friendly relations between the two countries 
were established by his excellency the great leader President 
Kim Il-song and the late Prime Minister Zulfiqar Ali Bhutto and 
are growing in strength today. 
  The DPRK has wrought amazing miracles in different sectors 
of 
the national economy under the wise guidance of his excellency 
the great leader President Kim Il-song, she said. 
  To have his excellency respected Kim Chong-il as the 
successor to the revolutionary cause pioneered by his excellency 
the great leader President Kim Il-song and as the dear leader is 
a firm guarantee for more solid political stability and eternal 
prosperity of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, she 
said. 
  She told the ambassador that the Pakistani Government would 
strengthen and further develop friendly relations with the DPRK 
in political, economic, cultural and all other fields. 

