<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Party Leaders Greet Kim Il-song </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2901044394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0411 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2901044394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- The great leader 
President Kim Il-song received from party leaders of different 
countries messages supporting his New Year address. 
  General Secretary Renan Raffo Munoz and International 
Secretary Guillermo Herrera Montecinos of the Central Committee 
of the Peruvian Communist Party in their message said that the 
Political Committee of the Central Committee of their party 
adopted a decision fully supporting the New Year address. 
  They said 1993 was a historic year in which the Democratic 
People's Republic of Korea won victory in the political and 
military confrontation with the enemy, pushed ahead with 
socialist economic construction, and made strenuous efforts for 
the reunification of the country on the principle of 
independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity, 
thus proving the validity of the revolutionary line of the 
Workers' Party of Korea. 
  Madhav Kumar Nepal, general secretary of the Central 
Committee of the Nepal Communist Party (United 
Marxism-Leninism), in his message said that his party and all 
the progressive people of Nepal fully support the Korean 
people's just cause of the reunification of divided Korea and 
the solution of the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula. "We 
hold that the United Nations should adopt an impartial and 
correct policy for peace and security on the Korean peninsula," 
he urged. 
  National General Secretary of the Socialist Political Action 
Party of Peru Gustavo Mohme Ryona, President of the National 
Executive Committee of the Left Revolutionary Union of Peru 
Angel Castro Lavarello and General Secretary of the People's 
Unity Party of Tunisia Mohamed Bel Hadj Amor in their messages 
expressed full support to the principled stand for the 
independent and peaceful reunification of Korea and the stand 
for a durable peace on the Korean peninsula which was put 
forward by President Kim Il-song in his New Year address. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

