<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Il-song's New Year Address Reported Abroad </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2901104894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1005 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2901104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- The New Year address 
of the great leader President Kim Il-song was reported by the 
British paper NEW WORLD, the Romanian paper NATIUNEA, the 
Brazilean paper A CLASE OPERARIA and Radio Citta Aperta of Italy. 
  Seminars on the New Year address were held by the group for 
the study of the chuche idea of the Commercial College of 
Uganda, the group for the study of the chuche idea of teachers 
of the Chambogo Polytechnical College of Uganda, the Makonde 
group for the study of the chuche idea in Chinhoyi, Zimbabwe, 
and the chuche idea study group of the Voluntary Work Camps' 
Association of Nigeria. 
  The speakers quoted President Kim Il-song as saying in his 
New Year address that last year the Korean people foiled the 
enemy's challenge and aggressive moves and honorably defended 
the dignity and security of their socialist motherland, thus 
fully demonstrating the unbreakable spirit of chuche Korea, that 
this was a victory of the revolutionary line of the Workers' 
Party of Korea and a great victory of the single-hearted unity 
of the leader, the party and the masses. 
  They said however desperately the imperialists may attempt 
to 
destroy the socialist system of Korea, it is a mistake and 
stressed that the just cause of the Korean people is invincible. 
  A reading session and a lecture on the New Year address were 
held at the cultural centre of Egypt. 

</TEXT>

