<F P=103> SK3001095194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 30 (KCNA) -- Papers here today 
observe the 25th anniversary of the opening of diplomatic 
relations between Korea and Equatorial Guinea. 
  The Equatorial Guinean people are now striving for national 
unity, social stability and economic redressment, rejecting 
imperialists' intervention, says NODONG SINMUN in a by-lined 
article, and goes on: 
  The Government of Equatorial Guinea maintains the principle 
of solving its problems by its people's efforts. 
  The Korean people rejoice at successes made by the 
Equatorial 
Guinean people in the building of a new life. 
  To strengthen and develop the Korea-Equatorial Guinea 
friendship is beneficial to the building of a new society in the 
two countries. 
  A signed article of MINJU CHOSON says that the Korean people 
wish the Equatorial Guinean people greater success in their 
struggle to build an independent new Equatorial Guinea, 
believing that the friendly and cooperative relations between 
the two peoples will grow stronger and develop in the future. 

