<H3> <TI>   Hosokawa Heads Office for Trade Complaints </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0102011194 Tokyo KYODO in English 0030 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0102011194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 1 KYODO -- Prime Minister Morihiro 
Hosokawa's cabinet decided Tuesday [1 February] to upgrade the 
existing Office of Trade and Investment Ombudsman (OTO) to an 
enlarged body, to deal with complaints about trade barriers. 
  The new organization will consist of cabinet ministers 
instead of vice administrative ministers, as was formerly the 
case with the OTO. The prime minister will serve as chief of 
the new body. 
  The upgrading of the OTO is in line with a proposal made 
last 
December by a government advisory panel that the OTO be expanded 
to deal more efficiently with trade complaints. 

</TEXT>

