<F P=102>  OW2701123394 Tokyo KYODO in English 1113 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2701123394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Nagoya, Jan. 27 KYODO -- Toyota Motor Corp. said 
Thursday [27 January] it has agreed with German automaker 
Volkswagen AG to extend their contract to make commercial 
vehicles in Germany. 
  Under the contract due to expire at the end of 1994, Toyota 
and Volkswagen have turned out Toyota's Hilux model and 
Volkswagen's Taro based on the Hilux at a Volkswagen factory in 
Hannover since 1989. 
  Toyota said the extended contract will be valid until the 
currently produced models give way to new ones, but that it is 
not yet decided whether to extend it again after that time. 
  The Hannover factory produced some 9,000 units last year and 
expects to keep production volume unchanged from last year's 
level in light of a weak European auto market. 

