  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 27 KYODO -- Japan on Thursday [27 
January] agreed with Jamaica on rescheduling of Japanese loans 
to the country, government officials said. 
  The agreement covers a total of 1.416 million yen worth of 
capital and interest payments due on September 30, 1995. 
  The rescheduled debt is part of loans to Jamaica by the 
